attachments.title: Pretty Playa Things (Eric's Mustache Goes To Burning Man) by The M Machine
attachments.text:
First of all, just wanted to acknowledge that Swardy was at his sister’s wedding in Maine, so he was sorely missed at BM this year :( :( :(

That being said, with this set, I tried to put together the most feel-good, melodic techno songs I could find. Some tracks are favorites from many years ago and some I just found in the past months. Burning Man was truly one of the most beautiful and unique experiences of my life (I realize that everyone says that…I don’t care). 

I do want to acknowledge the lack of M Machine music in this set. Honestly, I’ve never once been able to play a set full of pure melodic techno/house stuff. Always wanted to, but never got the chance till that night. Afterwards a few die-hard M Machine fans came up and told me that they loved the set, even if it was not in any way what they had expected to hear. We were there together experiencing something new, and honestly, that was what made my BM experience so great! There was so much art I’d never imagined before, so much music I’d never heard before and seemingly endless interactions with hilariously unique and awesome people. Thanks to Ego Trip for hosting the party and all who came out that night. Can’t wait to do it all again next year...

- Eric

JackLDN - Deep House London Mixtape #060 by Deep House London
attachments.text:
♫ Download ♫:
<http://www.deephouseamsterdam.com/london/mix-060-by-jackldn>

JackLNDN is one part classical technician and two parts main room club surgeon.  He’s simultaneously a mixture of centuries of European musical heritage and a sneak preview of the future.

As a producer and DJ, he has quickly established himself as a character whose work is quickly drawing attention for its freshness and whose potential is seemingly endless.  In his time on earth, LNDN has spent more time performing and playing music than most do in a lifetime.

On the production side, he started gleaning tips from friend Harry Wolfman and combined that with his knowledge of Logic and other bits of his training. Ever since, he has been slaving away in the studio, developing a variety of his unique strains of dance music. The linchpin of the sound has always been house, but filtered through an ever-evolving set of lenses: progressive, pop, jazz, and beyond.

Young JackLNDN is now poised to move large congregations himself. His remix and original production slate is stacked, in addition to his weekly DJ slots. This classical-turned-dance prodigy has got the musical chops and attention to detail so often lacking in dance music.

With his well received Ultra Records debut ‘All I See’ now available, and sets spanning Lollapalooza to Electric Zoo, we thought it was high time to bring the man himself on board for an exclusive mixtape.
